{{Infobox website | name = Glucosio | logo = Glucosio_Logo.png | screenshot = [[File:Glucosio For Android Screenshot.png|200px|Glucosio for Android]] | caption = Glucosio for Android 0.9.4 | url = {{URL|https://www.glucosio.org}} | commercial = No | location_country = USA | type = [[Open-source software]] | registration = Not required for viewing | creators = Benjamin Kerensa, Paolo Rotolo, Priyanka Nag, Elio Qoshi and Satyajit Sahoo | author = | launch date = 2015 | current status = Active }}
'''Glucosio''' is a free and [[Open-source software|open source]] project, created in 2015 by a group of open source developers to develop [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]] and Firefox OS apps for [[Diabetes management software|diabetes management]] and research.
== History ==
Glucosio was started by a group of open source developers in June 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Team - Glucosio|url = http://www.glucosio.org/team|accessdate = 2015-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = The Glucosio Project|url = http://benjaminkerensa.com/2015/07/08/the-glucosio-project|website = Benjamin Kerensa|accessdate = 2015-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Developer creates an open source glucose monitoring and tracking app he can trust|url = http://www.itworld.com/article/2989962/open-source-tools/developer-creates-an-open-source-glucose-monitoring-and-tracking-app-he-can-trust.html|website = ITworld|accessdate = 2015-10-08}}</ref> Glucosio consists of a Research [[Application programming interface|API]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] Application, and [[iOS]] Application. A unique feature of Glucosio is the ability for diabetics to opt into sharing anonymous glucose data with diabetes researchers via the research [[Application programming interface|API]].
Glucosio's project code is available on Github under the GPLv3 License<ref>{{Cite web|title = Glucosio|url = https://github.com/glucosio|website = GitHub|accessdate = 2015-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Glucosio Licensing Policy - Glucosio|url = http://www.glucosio.org/licensing/|accessdate = 2015-09-17}}</ref> for users who wish to build their app from scratch or contribute to the open source project, but is also published in the Google Play Store<ref>{{Cite web|title = Glucosio: Diabetes Tracker - Android Apps on Google Play|url = https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.glucosio.android|website = play.google.com|accessdate = 2015-10-12}}</ref>
