{{Infobox person | name = Terty Ivanovich Filippov | image = Filippov Terty Ivanovitsch (1825-1899).jpg | caption = | birthname = Тертий Иванович Филиппов | birth_date = {{Birth date|1825|1|5|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Rzhev]], [[Tver Governorate]], [[Russian Empire]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1899|12|12|1825|1|5|df=y}} | death_place = [[Saint Petersburg]], Russia | occupation = folklorist, journalist, church and state official | years_active = | spouse = | website = | awards = }} '''Terty Ivanovich Filippov''' (Тертий Иванович Филиппов; 5 January 1825 in [[Rzhev]], [[Tver Governorate]], [[Russian Empire]] &ndash; 12 December 1899 in [[Saint Petersburg]], Russian Empire) was a Russian [[folklorist]], [[singer]], [[pedagogue]], the Honorary member of the [[Saint Petersburg Academy of Sciences]]. As a [[journalist]], Filippov contributed mostly to [[Mikhail Pogodin|Pogodin]]'s ''[[Moskvityanin]]'', [[Mikhail Katkov|Katkov]]'s ''[[Russky Vestnik]]'' and ''[[Russkaya Beseda]]'', the magazine he was a co-founder of. In 1857-1864 Filippov served as a [[Russian Orthodox Church]] official. In 1889-1899 he was the Chairman of the [[:ru:Государственный контроль Российской империи|Russian State Control]] committee.<ref name="muz_enc">{{cite web | author = Malinina, L.Yu.| date = | url = http://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/enc_music/7891/%D0%A4%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%BF%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%B2|title = Filippov, Terty Ivanovich| publisher = The Music Encyclopedia. Moscow. Sovetsky Kompozitor. 1973-1982| accessdate = 2015-01-13}}</ref><ref name="rulex">{{cite web | author = | date = | url = http://www.rulex.ru/01210146.htm|title = Filippov, Terty Ivanovich| publisher = The Great Biographical Dictionary| accessdate = 2015-01-13}}</ref>
